        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5185",
        "content": "For why is it more lawful to satiate one's hunger and thirst than to drive away one's melancholy?",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5185_24772_000016_000005",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5185/24772/5185_24772_000016_000005.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5185",
        "content": "Therefore, to make use of what comes in our way, and to enjoy it as much as possible (not to the point of satiety, for that would not be enjoyment) is the part of a wise man.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5185_24772_000016_000007",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5185/24772/5185_24772_000016_000007.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5185",
        "content": "For the human body is composed of very numerous parts, of diverse nature, which continually stand in need of fresh and varied nourishment, so that the whole body may be equally capable of performing all the actions, which follow from the necessity of its own nature; and, consequently, so that the mind may also be equally capable of understanding many things simultaneously.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-normal_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very low"
    },
    {
